Big Laughs with Comedian Pete Lee*

We’ve done Big Band… let’s do Big Laughs with Comedian Pete Lee! Raised in Wisconsin by divorced parents and a 19 inch TV, he was destined for entertainment. Pete Lee was the first standup comedian to get a standing ovation on The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon, and has been named a regular on the show. Pete Lee’s credits also include NBC’s Last Comic Standing, CBS Soap Opera As The World Turns. a Comedy Central Half Hour Special, his own web show on MSN.com called New York Minute:30, a writer and cast member on FUSE TV’s Video on Trial and the NFL Network’s Top 10’s, VH1’s Best Week Ever, and CBS’s Late Show with David Letterman.

Currently, Pete is a cast member of TruTV’s Greatest Ever, hosts his own segment on Nickelodeon’s Nick Toons, called NFL Rush. He’s also a regular on TruTV’s Comedy Knockout and Comedy Central’s Roast Battle. Additionally, he was hired by the Duck Dynasty folks to be a writer/producer, and he helped develop the hit Duck Dynasty spin-off Going Siral. He also starred in a documentary titled I Need You to Kill that is now available on iTunes and Amazon. Most recently, Pete became a writer/cast member on the hit show This Week at the Comedy Cellar on Comedy Central.
On Thursday, September 19th, Pete Lee will join us for this year’s Big Laugh in the Hornung Student Center. You won’t want to miss it!
